00:00:00.859 --> 00:00:03.179
hi everyone this is Paul J. Adam

00:00:03.179 --> 00:00:06.779
and I'm recording a demonstration video

00:00:06.779 --> 00:00:11.019
to show you how to use the VoiceOver Practice

00:00:11.019 --> 00:00:15.339
feature in the VoiceOver Accessibility Settings so if you open your settings

00:00:15.339 --> 00:00:15.830
app

00:00:15.830 --> 00:00:19.350
and go to general then Accessibility

00:00:19.350 --> 00:00:22.510
when you go into voice-over

00:00:22.510 --> 00:00:26.090
on you can actually turn on

00:00:26.090 --> 00:00:30.410
a practice area if I turn VoiceOver on

00:00:30.410 --> 00:00:37.079
Screen Reader: VoiceOver On, Paul: now I can go to VoiceOver Practice

00:00:37.079 --> 00:00:43.450
SR: VoiceOver Practice, button

00:00:43.450 --> 00:00:46.800
SR: VoiceOver Practice, Handwriting help, button

00:00:46.800 --> 00:00:50.200
Touch Select item under your finger

00:00:50.200 --> 00:00:55.020
Paul: so any gesture that I attempt in this voiceover practice area it will tell me what it does

00:00:55.020 --> 00:00:58.500
depending on the finger combinations and the swipe

00:00:58.500 --> 00:01:01.660
Two finger single tap pause or continue speech

00:01:01.660 --> 00:01:05.199
two finger flick down read page started at selected item

00:01:05.199 --> 00:01:10.820
two finger flick up read page starting at the top

00:01:10.820 --> 00:01:14.000
Three finger single tap, Speak page number or rows being displayed.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:19.000
Three finger double tap Toggle speech on and off.

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:23.000
Three finger triple tap Toggle screen curtain on and off.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:27.000
Four finger single tap near top of screen. Move to the first element.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:29.500
Four finger single tap near bottom of screen Move to the last element.

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:32.000
Flick right. Move to next item.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:34.000
Flick left. Move to previous item.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:36.000
Rotate clockwise select next rotor setting

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:41.000
Rotate counterclockwise Select previous rotor setting.

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:43.000
Flick down Move to next item using rotor setting.

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:46.000
Flick up Move to previous item using rotor setting.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:50.000
Paul: OK so that is just a simple demonstration

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:54.000
of the VoiceOver Practice Feature

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:57.000
SR: VoiceOver off

